#!/bin/bash
# klow-help - Display available commands and usage

cat << 'EOF'
Klowalski PC Access Commands
============================

READ OPERATIONS (safe, no modifications):
  klow-tree [path] [depth]    Show directory tree (default depth: 3)
  klow-list [path]            List directory contents
  klow-read <file>            Read file contents
  klow-status                 Show system status (disk, memory, uptime)
  klow-manifest [folder]      Show/edit folder descriptions

FILE OPERATIONS (controlled):
  klow-mark-delete <file> [reason]   Move file to trash (not actual delete)
  klow-organize <file> <dest>        Move file to KlowalskiWorkspace/

WORKSPACE (full access in sandbox):
  klow-workspace <command>    Run command inside KlowalskiWorkspace/

SYSTEM (restricted):
  klow-shutdown [seconds]     Shutdown PC (0-3600 sec delay, default: 60)
  klow-shutdown-cancel        Cancel pending shutdown

UTILITY:
  klow-help                   Show this help message

PATHS:
  Workspace: /mnt/c/Users/Daniel/Desktop/KlowalskiWorkspace/
  Trash:     /mnt/c/Users/Daniel/Desktop/KlowalskiTrash/
  Logs:      /home/klowalski/logs/

BLOCKED (cannot access):
  - .ssh directories
  - .env files and credentials
  - AppData folder
  - Windows system directories
EOF
